name: meltan
pokemon_entry: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

name: melmetal
pokemon_entry: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.

name: grookey
pokemon_entry: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

name: thwackey
pokemon_entry: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.

name: rillaboom
pokemon_entry: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

name: scorbunny
pokemon_entry: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon's body. Once that happens, it's ready to fight at full power.

name: raboot
pokemon_entry: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it from the cold and enables it to use hotter fire moves.

name: cinderace
pokemon_entry: It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched.

name: sobble
pokemon_entry: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won't be able to resist weeping.

name: drizzile
pokemon_entry: A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.

name: inteleon
pokemon_entry: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

name: skwovet
pokemon_entry: Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.

name: greedent
pokemon_entry: It stashes berries in its tailâso many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn't notice the loss.

name: rookidee
pokemon_entry: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battleâeven a defeat increases its strength a bit.

name: corvisquire
pokemon_entry: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.

name: corviknight
pokemon_entry: This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.

name: blipbug
pokemon_entry: A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn't.

name: dottler
pokemon_entry: It barely moves, but it's still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.

name: orbeetle
pokemon_entry: It's famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.

name: nickit
pokemon_entry: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.

name: thievul
pokemon_entry: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.

name: gossifleur
pokemon_entry: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

name: eldegoss
pokemon_entry: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

name: wooloo
pokemon_entry: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

name: dubwool
pokemon_entry: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You'll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

name: chewtle
pokemon_entry: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.

name: drednaw
pokemon_entry: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

name: yamper
pokemon_entry: This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.

name: boltund
pokemon_entry: This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.

name: rolycoly
pokemon_entry: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.

name: carkol
pokemon_entry: It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokémon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region.

name: coalossal
pokemon_entry: It's usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: applin
pokemon_entry: It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it's just an apple and nothing more.

name: flapple
pokemon_entry: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.

name: appletun
pokemon_entry: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on.

name: silicobra
pokemon_entry: As it digs, it swallows sand and stores it in its neck pouch. The pouch can hold more than 17 pounds of sand.

name: sandaconda
pokemon_entry: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.

name: cramorant
pokemon_entry: Route 9, Axew's Eye, Bridge Field, Lake of Outrage, Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles: Giant's Cap, Hammerlocke Hills

name: arrokuda
pokemon_entry: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It's very proud of that jaw.

name: barraskewda
pokemon_entry: This Pokémon has a jaw that's as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda's flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.

name: toxel
pokemon_entry: It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows.

name: toxtricity
pokemon_entry: Max Raid Battles: East Lake Axewell, Giant's Cap, Giant's Mirror, Hammerlocke Hills, Lake of Outrage, Motostoke Riverbank, North Lake Miloch

name: toxtricity
pokemon_entry: Max Raid Battles: East Lake Axewell, Giant's Cap, Giant's Mirror, Hammerlocke Hills, Lake of Outrage, Motostoke Riverbank, North Lake Miloch

name: sizzlipede
pokemon_entry: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

name: centiskorch
pokemon_entry: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

name: clobbopus
pokemon_entry: It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

name: grapploct
pokemon_entry: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.

name: sinistea
pokemon_entry: Glimwood TangleMax Raid Battles: Stony Wilderness, Watchtower Ruins

name: polteageist
pokemon_entry: Max Raid Battles: Stony Wilderness, Watchtower Ruins

name: hatenna
pokemon_entry: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures' emotions. If you don't have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.

name: hattrem
pokemon_entry: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.

name: hatterene
pokemon_entry: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.

name: impidimp
pokemon_entry: Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.

name: morgrem
pokemon_entry: When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, it's trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.

name: grimmsnarl
pokemon_entry: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.

name: obstagoon
pokemon_entry: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shoutâthis move is known as Obstruct.

name: perrserker
pokemon_entry: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.

name: cursola
pokemon_entry: Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokémon's core spirit.

name: sirfetch'd
pokemon_entry: Only Farfetch'd that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon's leek withers, it will retire from combat.

name: mr_rime
pokemon_entry: It's highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.

name: runerigus
pokemon_entry: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.

name: milcery
pokemon_entry: This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.

name: alcremie
pokemon_entry: Max Raid Battles: Bridge Field, Lake of OutrageGigantamax Raid Battles: Bridge Field

name: falinks
pokemon_entry: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass's orders are absolute.

name: pincurchin
pokemon_entry: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.

name: snom
pokemon_entry: It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.

name: frosmoth
pokemon_entry: Icy scales fall from its wings like snow as it flies over fields and mountains. The temperature of its wings is less than -290 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: stonjourner
pokemon_entry: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun's descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.

name: eiscue
pokemon_entry: Trade from Shield

name: eiscue
pokemon_entry: Trade from Shield

name: indeedee
pokemon_entry: Glimwood Tangle, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles: Bridge Field, East Lake Axewell, Hammerlocke Hills, Motostoke Riverbank, Rolling Fields, Stony Wilderness

name: indeedee
pokemon_entry: Glimwood Tangle, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles: Bridge Field, East Lake Axewell, Hammerlocke Hills, Motostoke Riverbank, Rolling Fields, Stony Wilderness

name: morpeko
pokemon_entry: Route 7, Route 9, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles: Giant's Mirror, Lake of Outrage, Motostoke Riverbank

name: cufant
pokemon_entry: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It's also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.

name: copperajah
pokemon_entry: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.

name: dracozolt
pokemon_entry: In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.

name: arctozolt
pokemon_entry: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.

name: dracovish
pokemon_entry: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.

name: arctovish
pokemon_entry: Though it's able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.

name: duraludon
pokemon_entry: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

name: dreepy
pokemon_entry: After being reborn as a ghost Pokémon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.

name: drakloak
pokemon_entry: It's capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.

name: dragapult
pokemon_entry: When it isn't battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.

name: zacian
pokemon_entry: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokémon absorbs metal particles, transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.

name: zamazenta
pokemon_entry: In times past, it worked together with a king of the people to save the Galar region. It absorbs metal that it then uses in battle.

name: eternatus
pokemon_entry: Energy Plant

name: kubfu
pokemon_entry: Kubfu trains hard to perfect its moves. The moves it masters will determine which form it takes when it evolves.

name: urshifu_single_strike_style
pokemon_entry: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.

name: urshifu_rapid_strike_style
pokemon_entry: It's believed that this Pokémon modeled its fighting style on the flow of a riverâsometimes rapid, sometimes calm.

name: zarude
pokemon_entry: Event Only

name: regieleki
pokemon_entry: This Pokémon is a cluster of electrical energy. It’s said that removing the rings on Regieleki’s body will unleash the Pokémon’s latent power.

name: regidrago
pokemon_entry: An academic theory proposes that Regidrago’s arms were once the head of an ancient dragon Pokémon. The theory remains unproven.

name: glastrier
pokemon_entry: Glastrier emits intense cold from its hooves. It’s also a belligerent Pokémon—anything it wants, it takes by force.

name: spectrier
pokemon_entry: It probes its surroundings with all its senses save one—it doesn’t use its sense of sight. Spectrier’s kicks are said to separate soul from body.
